  "prompt": "Why is my Kindle gift card not working on Amazon?",
  "response": "There are several reasons why your Kindle gift card might not be working on Amazon. Here's a breakdown of the most common culprits and how to troubleshoot them:\n\n**1. Incorrect Entry or Typos:**\n\n*   **Carefully re-enter the code:** Double-check the gift card number and any security codes. It's easy to mix up letters and numbers (e.g., O and 0, I and 1, S and 5). Try copy-pasting the code directly if possible.\n*   **Check for extra spaces:** Ensure there are no extra spaces before, after, or within the code.\n\n**2. Activation Issues:**\n\n*   **Card not activated:** If the gift card was purchased in a physical store, the cashier may not have properly activated it.  You'll need to contact the store where it was purchased and have them activate the card. You might need your receipt.\n*   **New Gift Card - Wait a few hours:** In some cases, especially with digital gift cards, it can take a few hours for the card to fully activate in Amazon's system.  Try again later.\n\n**3. Redemption Issues:**\n\n*   **Already redeemed:** If you've already redeemed the gift card to your Amazon account, it won't work again. Check your Amazon account balance to see if the funds are there.\n*   **Account Issues:**\n    *   **Account Region Mismatch:** If your Amazon account region (e.g., US, UK, Canada) doesn't match the region the gift card was issued in, it won't work. For example, a US gift card won't work on an Amazon UK account. You may need to change the country setting in your Amazon account.\n    *   **Account Restrictions:**  In rare cases, there might be restrictions on your Amazon account that prevent gift card redemption. Contact Amazon customer service to inquire about this.\n\n**4. Expiration:**\n\n*   **Expired Gift Card:** Some gift cards do have expiration dates, although this is less common with Amazon gift cards. Check the fine print on the gift card or packaging for an expiration date.\n\n**5. Technical Issues:**\n\n*   **Amazon Website/App Problems:** Sometimes, there can be temporary glitches on Amazon's website or app. Try again later or try using a different device (computer, phone, tablet).\n*   **Browser/Cache Issues:**  Sometimes, old data stored in your browser's cache can cause problems. Try clearing your browser's cache and cookies or try using a different browser.\n\n**6. Phishing/Scam Attempts:**\n\n*   **Suspect Gift Card:** If you received the gift card from an untrusted source or something seems \"off\" about it, it could be a fake or part of a scam. Do not attempt to use it and report it to Amazon.\n\n**Troubleshooting Steps to Try:**\n\n1.  **Check Your Amazon Account Balance:** Go to \"Your Account\" on Amazon, then \"Gift Cards,\" and look for your gift card balance.  This will confirm if the card was previously redeemed.\n\n2.  **Try a Different Device/Browser:** Rule out a device-specific issue.\n\n3.  **Wait and Try Again:** If it's a newly purchased digital gift card, give it a few hours to activate.\n\n4.  **Review the Gift Card Terms and Conditions:** Look for any specific instructions or restrictions related to the card.\n\n5.  **Contact Amazon Customer Service IMMEDIATELY:** This is the most important step if you've ruled out the obvious causes. Explain the situation clearly and provide the gift card number. Amazon's customer service can investigate the issue and help resolve it. You can usually find a \"Help\" or \"Contact Us\" link at the bottom of Amazon's website or in the app.  Look for options to chat with an agent or request a call back.\n    *   **Be prepared to provide:**\n        *   The gift card number.\n        *   Proof of purchase (if you have it).\n        *   Details about where and when you purchased the card.\n        *   Your Amazon account information.\n\n**Important Notes:**\n\n*   **Keep the Gift Card Safe:**  Treat a gift card like cash. Don't share the code with anyone you don't trust.\n*   **Report Suspicious Activity:** If you believe your gift card has been compromised or you suspect a scam, report it to Amazon immediately.\n\nBy following these troubleshooting steps and contacting Amazon customer service if needed, you should be able to resolve the issue with your Kindle gift card. Good luck!\n",
